    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "Various parts of this *+2 resilient half plate* are forged into the shape of a lion\u2019s head. The golden lion heads grant you a commanding presence and seem to actively growl at your enemies, granting you a +2 item bonus to Intimidation.  \n  \nThe lions on the armor work in tandem with the lion on a *lion's shield*. If you critically hit with the *lion\u2019s shield* using Lion Bite, the lions on the armor roar in support of the shield, causing the target of the shield\u2019s Strike to become frightened 1.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 98,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "invest",
            "aonid": 2799,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "invest",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Invested",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "GM Core",
            "page": 219,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
